      &quot;The 'problem on their end' was using a non-unique ID as a unique ID. Nothing more, nothing less. &quot;<br /><br />And they knew what sort of problems this would cause when the developers changed the algorithms to only recognize transaction IDs with no padding zeros - in 2011 - and everyone else updated their code to reflect this change.  Yes, Mt. Gox is a little lax and guilty of not keeping their eye on the birdie, but nothing worse than that.
      
    </div>
