    <div class="body">
      While the price on Mt Gox continues to fall as their users scramble for the door, what I find interesting is that other exchanges such as Bitstamp appear to have been only moderately affected by the ongoing implosion of Mt Gox. This could be a sign that if Mt Gox actually goes bankrupt, other exchanges will have no problem carrying on without them. <br /><br />It will be very interesting to see what happens when a real U.S. based exchange comes online once the regulations get sorted out.
      
    </div>
